SIMPLE: sickness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sickness
<hw>Sick"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>se⟦oacute⟧cness</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state
of being sick or diseased; illness; disease or malady.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I do lament the <qex>sickness</qex> of the king.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Trust not too much your now resistless charms;⟦br⟧
Those, age or <qex>sickness</qex> soon or late disarms.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Nausea; qualmishness; <as>as, <ex>sickness</ex> of
stomach</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Illness; disease; malady. See
<er>Illness</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sicle</ent>⟦br⟧
